## Gap Analysis (before upgrade)

The target spec was a 22-line migration stub with 0% content compliance. Everything was built from scratch.

## What Was Written

### `param_ref-spec.md` (~1,500 lines, ~95% compliance)

**Domain:** `param-ref-svc` — the authoritative source for all controlled vocabularies (reference data catalogs) across the platform. SAP equivalent: DDIC domains, SM30 table maintenance, T-tables (T005/TCURC/T002/T052).

**Key content added:**
- **§3 Domain Model:** `Catalog` aggregate root (12-attribute table, 2-state lifecycle) + `CatalogCode` child entity (12-attribute table, immutability invariants, validity period) + `CatalogRef` value object for cross-service contracts. 3 enumerations (CatalogScope, CatalogStatus, CodeStatus).
- **§4 Business Rules:** 9 rules (BR-REF-001 through 009) — uniqueness, immutability, scope access control, deprecation irreversibility, validity coherence.
- **§5 Use Cases:** 10 use cases including the machine-facing validate endpoint (UC-REF-008) and bulk import/export.
- **§6 REST API:** 13 endpoints fully documented; validate endpoint returns `200 { valid, reason }` rather than error codes (D-REF-003).
- **§7 Events:** 3 published events (catalog.created, catalog.updated with `changedCodes`, catalog.deprecated). Semi-thin deviation justified (D-REF-001).
- **§8 Tables:** `ref_catalog`, `ref_catalog_code` (with `custom_fields JSONB` + GIN index), `ref_outbox_events`.
- **§12 Extension Points:** `CatalogCode` is extensible; `Catalog` is not. All 5 extension types covered.
- **§13 Migration:** SAP T005/TCURC/T002/T052 mapping; deprecated SAP codes migrate as `status=DEPRECATED`.

**Decisions recorded (§14.2):** D-REF-001 through D-REF-005

**Open questions raised (§14.3 + status file):** Q-REF-001 (ownerSuite registry), Q-REF-002 (PLATFORM multi-tenancy model), Q-REF-003 (auto-namespace registration), Q-REF-004 (tenant deletion), Q-REF-005 (PLATFORM catalog tenant_id), Q-REF-006 (port 8100 confirmation)

